#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:0.5"
msgid "60. Cīvaraapanidhānasikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.60\">Monks’ Confession 60: the training rule on "
"hiding robes</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.123
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.60.1\">Bu-Pc.60.1</a><a class=\"pts-vp-en\""
" id=\"BD.2.414\">BD.2.414</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1152</a>At one time the "
"Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū asannihitaparikkhārā honti."
msgstr ""
"On one occasion when the monks from the group of seventeen had not put away "
"their requisites,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.3"
msgid ""
"Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sattarasavaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pattampi cīvarampi "
"apanidhenti."
msgstr "the monks from the group of six hid their bowls and robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.4"
msgid "Sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The monks from the group of seventeen said to them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.5"
msgid "“dethāvuso, amhākaṃ pattampi cīvarampī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Give <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.123\">Vin.4.123</a> us our bowls and "
"robes.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.6"
msgid "Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū hasanti, te rodanti."
msgstr ""
"The monks from the group of six laughed, but the monks from the group of "
"seventeen cried.</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.7"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "<p>The monks asked them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.8"
msgid "“kissa tumhe, āvuso, rodathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Why are you crying?”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.9"
msgid ""
"“Ime, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū amhākaṃ pattampi cīvarampi apanidhentī”ti."
msgstr ""
"<p>“Because the monks from the group of six have hidden our bowls and "
"robes.”</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.10"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1153</a>The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.11"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.12"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ pattampi cīvarampi "
"apanidhessantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six hide the bowls and robes of other "
"monks?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.13"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pattampi cīvarampi apanidhethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.14"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.15"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.16"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhūnaṃ pattampi cīvarampi "
"apanidhessatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you hide the bowls and robes of other monks?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.17"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it ..."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.18"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc3
#. VAR: hasāpekkhopi → hassāpekkhopi (bj, s1-3) | hāsāpekkho pi (pts1)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:1.19"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhussa pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā nisīdanaṃ vā sūcigharaṃ vā "
"kāyabandhanaṃ vā apanidheyya vā apanidhāpeyya vā, antamaso hasāpekkhopi, "
"pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2>\n"
"<p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1154</a>‘If a monk hides another monk’s "
"bowl, robe-cloth, sitting-mat, needle-case, or belt, or he gets it hidden, "
"even if just for a laugh, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc4
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.60.2\"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-"
"Pc.60.2.1\">Bu-Pc.60.2.1</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1155</a><term>A</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>whoever …</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b><b class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "<term>Monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"<gloss>… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhussāti"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.415\">BD.2.415</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1156</a><term>Another monk’s</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.7"
msgid "aññassa bhikkhussa."
msgstr "<gloss>a different monk’s.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.8"
msgid "Patto nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1157</a><term>Bowl</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.9"
msgid "dve pattā—"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.10"
msgid "ayopatto, mattikāpatto."
msgstr "<gloss>an iron bowl or a ceramic bowl.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.11"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1158</a><term>Robe-cloth</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.12"
msgid "channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ, vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>one of the six kinds of robe-cloth,<span class=\"note\" hidden>The "
"six are linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp; see <span class=\""
"ref\">MS.3.1595</span>.</span> but not smaller than what can be transferred.<"
"span class=\"note\" hidden>This means not smaller than 8 by 4 standard (<i "
"lang=\"pi\">sugata</i>) finger-breadths, or 16 by 8 cm; see <span class=\""
"ref\">Kkh.</span> and BMC I, pp. 565-566.</span></gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.13"
msgid "Nisīdanaṃ nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1159</a><term>Sitting-mat</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.14"
msgid "sadasaṃ vuccati."
msgstr "<gloss>one with a border is what is meant.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.15"
msgid "Sūcigharaṃ nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1160</a><term>Needle-case</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.16"
msgid "sasūcikaṃ vā asūcikaṃ vā."
msgstr "<gloss>with or without needles.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.17"
msgid "Kāyabandhanaṃ nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1161</a><term>Belt</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.18"
msgid "dve kāyabandhanāni—"
msgstr "<gloss>there are two kinds of belts:"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.19"
msgid "paṭṭikā, sūkarantakaṃ."
msgstr ""
"those made from strips of cloth and those made from pigs’ "
"intestines.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.20"
msgid "Apanidheyya vāti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1162</a><term>Hides</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.21"
msgid "sayaṃ apanidheti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>if he hides it himself, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.22"
msgid "Apanidhāpeyya vāti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1163</a><term>Gets […] hidden</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.23"
msgid "aññaṃ āṇāpesi, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "<gloss>if he asks another, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.24"
msgid "Sakiṃ āṇatto bahukampi apanidheti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he only asks once, then even if the other hides many things, he commits "
"one offense entailing confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.25"
msgid "Antamaso hasāpekkhopīti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1164</a><term>Even if just for a laugh</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.1.26"
msgid "kīḷādhippāyo."
msgstr "<gloss>aiming to have fun.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc14
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.2.1"
msgid ""
"Upasampanne upasampannasaññī pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā nisīdanaṃ vā sūcigharaṃ vā "
"kāyabandhanaṃ vā apanidheti vā apanidhāpeti vā, antamaso hasāpekkhopi, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.60.2.2\">Bu-Pc.60.2.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1165</a>If the other monk is fully ordained, and he perceives him as fully "
"ordained, and he hides his bowl or robe-cloth or sitting-mat or needle-case "
"or belt, or he gets it hidden, even if just for a laugh, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.2.2"
msgid "Upasampanne vematiko … pe …"
msgstr ""
"If the other monk is fully ordained, but he is unsure if he is, and he hides "
"his bowl or robe-cloth or sitting-mat or needle-case or belt, or he gets it "
"hidden, even if just for a laugh, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.2.3"
msgid ""
"upasampanne anupasampannasaññī pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā nisīdanaṃ vā sūcigharaṃ "
"vā kāyabandhanaṃ vā apanidheti vā apanidhāpeti vā, antamaso hasāpekkhopi, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If the other monk is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as fully "
"ordained, and he hides his bowl or robe-cloth or sitting-mat or needle-case "
"or belt, or he gets it hidden, even if just for a laugh, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15, pts-vp-pli4.124
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.2.4"
msgid ""
"Aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ apanidheti vā apanidhāpeti vā, antamaso hasāpekkhopi, "
"āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1166</a>If he hides another requisite, or he gets it "
"hidden, even if just for a laugh, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.2.5"
msgid ""
"Anupasampannassa pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā aññaṃ vā parikkhāraṃ apanidheti vā "
"apanidhāpeti vā, antamaso hasāpekkhopi, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he hides the bowl or robe-cloth or other requisite of someone who is not "
"fully ordained, or he gets it hidden, even if just for a laugh, he commits "
"an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.2.6"
msgid "Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p>If the other person is not fully ordained, but he perceives him as fully "
"ordained, <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.416\">BD.2.416</a> he commits an "
"offense <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.124\">Vin.4.124</a> of wrong "
"conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.2.7"
msgid "Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the other person is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.2.8"
msgid "Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the other person is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive him as "
"fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.60.2.3\">Bu-Pc.60.2.3</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1167</a>There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.3.2"
msgid ""
"nahasādhippāyo, dunnikkhittaṃ paṭisāmeti, “dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā dassāmī”ti "
"paṭisāmeti, ummattakassa, ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if he is not aiming to have fun; if he puts away what has been improperly "
"put away; if he puts something away with the thought, “After giving a "
"teaching, I’ll give it back;” if he is insane; if he is the first "
"offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.3.3"
msgid "Cīvaraapanidhānasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1168</a>The tenth rule, the "
"training rule on hiding robes, is finished.</p>"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.3.4"
msgid "Surāpānavaggo chaṭṭho."
msgstr ""
"<p class=\"endchapter\">The sixth chapter on alcoholic drinks is "
"finished.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection summary">
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.3.5"
msgid "Tassuddānaṃ"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1169</a>This is the summary:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc19
#. VAR: hāso ca → toyañca (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.3.6"
msgid "Surā aṅguli hāso ca,"
msgstr ""
"<p><uddana><a class=\"wt-pa\">1170</a>Alcohol, finger, and laughter,<br>"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.3.7"
msgid "anādariyañca bhiṃsanaṃ;"
msgstr "And disrespect, scaring;<br>"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.3.8"
msgid "Jotinahānadubbaṇṇaṃ,"
msgstr "Fire, bathing, stain,<br>"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc60:2.3.9"
msgid "sāmaṃ apanidhena cāti."
msgstr "Himself, and with hiding.</uddana></p>"
